      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/57/1203",
      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يَنْسَى وَ هُوَ خَلْفَ اَلْإِمَامِ أَنْ يُسَبِّحَ فِي اَلسُّجُودِ أَوْ فِي اَلرُّكُوعِ أَوْ يَنْسَى أَنْ يَقُولَ بَيْنَ اَلسَّجْدَتَيْنِ شَيْئاً قَالَ «لَيْسَ عَلَيْهِ شَيْءٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1203 - Ammar al-Sabati narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\n\"I asked him about a man who, while praying behind an Imam, forgets to say the tasbih (glorification) during Sujood (prostration) or ruku' (bowing) or forgets to say something between the two prostrations.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no obligation upon him (no penalty).\""
        ]
      }
    },
